[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    123[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Strengthen the Prerequisites IAM row with per-consumer scoping: "EHR-audit-ingest Lambda role: parse vendor-specific audit-log feed, write canonical events to the audit-events stream only; no DynamoDB or Timestream access. App-audit-ingest Lambda role: similar narrow ingest scope. Identity-log-ingest Lambda role: parse IdP/VPN/auth logs, write canonical events; no read of workforce identity. Break-glass-ingest Lambda role: parse break-glass override events, write to the audit-events stream and the break-glass-ingest output. Identity-context-loader Lambda role: read from HRIS/IAM/scheduling sources, write to workforce-identity and workforce-schedule DynamoDB tables and patient-context table. Event-normalizer Lambda role: read from the audit-events stream, write canonical events; no read of workforce identity. Enrichment Lambda role: read on workforce-identity, workforce-schedule, patient-context for the event being enriched only; write enriched events downstream. Rules-engine Lambda role: read enriched events, write rule-flag outputs. Baseline-detector Lambda role: read on Timestream behavioral-baselines for the user being scored; write deviation scores. Graph-detector Lambda role: read on Neptune for the user-patient relationship being scored; write graph scores. Composite-scoring Lambda role: read scores from the prior detectors, write composite to scoring-history. Calibration Lambda role: read raw composite, write calibrated. Case-builder Lambda role: read scoring-history, workforce-identity, patient-context, Neptune; [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdynamodb:PutItem[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on case-state; [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mbedrock:InvokeModel[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on the configured Bedrock model; [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevents:PutEvents[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m to the case-bus only. Outcome-capture Lambda role: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdynamodb:UpdateItem[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on case-state for the case being captured; [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:PutObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on training-labels bucket only; [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevents:PutEvents[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m to the case-bus only. Privacy-office investigator UI roles: read case-state by case_id scoped by case-assignment; write outcome-event to the case-bus only. SIEM connector role: read case-state by case_id where case-class is in the SOC-relevant set (credential_compromise, lateral_movement) only; no read of curiosity-snooping cases. Privacy-office leadership roles: read aggregated subgroup-metrics view only; row-level read on case archives requires explicit elevation with documented purpose. Data-science roles: read on pseudonymized training-data view only; raw case data requires explicit elevation."[K
