[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    147[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies the IdP/VPN/auth log ingestion path and the HRIS/IAM/scheduling integration path with named representative vendors (Active Directory, Okta, Microsoft Entra ID; Workday, Oracle HCM, SAP SuccessFactors, UKG, Kronos, API Healthcare). But the per-source security posture is not specified: Okta and Entra ID expose system log APIs that use OAuth 2.0 with API keys; Active Directory typically requires either the Microsoft 365 audit log API (OAuth) or a domain-controller event-forwarding setup (Windows Event Forwarding); VPN logs typically come through SIEM forwarding (Splunk forwarders, syslog-over-TLS); Workday, Oracle HCM, and SAP SuccessFactors expose REST APIs with OAuth 2.0 and per-tenant client credentials; Kronos/UKG and API Healthcare expose either REST APIs or scheduled SFTP file drops.[K
