should be 1 because a single dropped event is a missed access pattern, a missed detector input, a missed case, or a missed breach-notification-clock initiation. Replay events from DLQ after fixing the root cause; for events older than the privacy-office case-grouping window relevant to the case being constructed, escalate to privacy-office-governance-committee review rather than auto-replay because the timing-of-detection is itself part of the program's safety case." Add a "DLQ and replay" bullet to "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" that ties the discipline to the existing disaster-recovery paragraph.[K
