[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    522[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe architectural backstop for these network paths is missing. Same shape as Recipe 3.8 N4 (HIE/claims feed) but the recipe-3.9-distinctive concern is identity-federation rather than data-flow.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    523[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    524[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add an external-organization-monitoring-network-path paragraph to the Variations-and-Extensions "External-organization monitoring" extension: "External-organization monitoring requires identity-federation infrastructure that the local monitoring system can integrate with. Bilateral SAML 2.0 or OIDC federation between the local IdP and each external organization's IdP carries the federated identity assertion through to the audit-event ingest layer; the workforce-identity enrichment layer recognizes federated identifiers and dispatches to per-organization context lookup. TEFCA-compliant identity federation under the QHIN framework is operationally distinct from bilateral federation; the QHIN broker handles the federation and the local system consumes federated identity assertions through a TEFCA-compliant connector. Per-organization scope-of-relationship documentation is maintained in a privacy-office-controlled DynamoDB table that drives the suppression-rule library for cross-organizational care relationships. The case-builder layer recognizes cross-organizational cases and dispatches to a separate review queue staffed by privacy-office staff with cross-organizational case-handling authority."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    525[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    526[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mFinding N4: PAM Tooling Network Integration for Privileged-User Separate Program Not Specified[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    527[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    528[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSeverity:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m LOW[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    529[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mExpert:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Networking / Architecture[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    530[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Variations-and-Extensions "Privileged-access management (PAM) integration" extension; Finding A3 (privileged-user separate program).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    531[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    532[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies PAM tooling integration as a Variations-level extension and names representative tools (CyberArk, BeyondTrust, HashiCorp Boundary). But the network-integration specifics are not specified. PAM tools typically use:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    533[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    534[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mBastion-host pattern with session recording.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m SSH or RDP sessions flow through a PAM-controlled bastion that records the session and emits per-session metadata events.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    535[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDatabase proxy with query logging.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Database connections flow through a PAM-controlled proxy that logs queries and emits per-query metadata events.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    536[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAPI gateway with request logging.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m API access flows through a PAM-controlled gateway that logs requests and emits per-request metadata events.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    537[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    538[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mEach path has different network requirements: bastion hosts typically require a dedicated VPC subnet and NAT gateway routing; database proxies typically integrate with VPC endpoints or PrivateLink to the database service; API gateways typically integrate with the AWS API Gateway or with a vendor-specific deployment. The PAM vendor's BAA posture and the data-residency posture for the session-recording archive matter for HIPAA.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    539[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    540[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mSame shape as the EHR-ingress and IdP-ingress findings (S4, S5).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    541[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    542[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a PAM-tooling-network-integration paragraph to the Variations-and-Extensions "PAM integration" extension: "PAM tooling typically uses bastion-host (SSH/RDP), database-proxy, and API-gateway patterns. Bastion hosts require a dedicated VPC subnet with appropriate routing; database proxies integrate with VPC endpoints or PrivateLink to the database service; API gateways integrate with the AWS API Gateway or a vendor-specific deployment. The PAM vendor's BAA posture must cover the session-recording archive (which contains PHI in clinical-database queries and integration-engine activity logs); session-recording data should be stored with customer-managed KMS encryption and retention aligned to the labor-and-legal documentation requirement. The PAM-tool-emitted per-session-or-per-query metadata flows into the audit-event pipeline as a [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpam_session[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m or [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpam_query[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m source-system class, enriched with privileged-user identity context, and scored by the privileged-user-specific detector bank (Finding A3)."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    543[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    544[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mVoice Reviewer[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    545[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    546[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhat's Done Well[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    547[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    548[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe opening cardiology-step-down-nurse vignette is publication-ready voice. The 11:47 p.m. on a Tuesday opening, the nurse who shares a last name with the patient and lives on the same street, the ninety seconds in the chart, the demographics and medication-list and discharge-plan views, the six audit events out of forty million that night, the legitimate user account at her usual workstation, the broad EHR access configured for clinical workflow flexibility rather than least-privilege, the absence of any VIP flag or rules-engine fire or daily-report notice, the three-week-later complaint from the patient about his cousin asking about a medication he hadn't told her about, the privacy-office investigation, the six-week timeline, the termination, the OCR breach notification, the civil suit, the local newspaper, and the CIO call from the CEO that begins with "explain to me how this happened" is the densest healthcare-access-monitoring framing in any cookbook recipe and is the closest the cookbook has come to operational reality of insider snooping. The closing reframe ("Not the Hollywood scenario where a foreign state actor exfiltrates ten million records") is the system reframe most first-time builders miss.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    549[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    550[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe "Healthcare has a specific structural problem that makes this hard" framing is the recipe's biggest pedagogical contribution. The "broad clinical access is not a bug but a feature" framing (clinicians need broad access because patients move between units, get cross-covered, end up in the ED at 3 a.m.; pulling permissions tighter solves the privacy problem and creates the patient-safety problem; patient safety wins every time) is exactly the design lesson that distinguishes mature healthcare access programs from generic UEBA deployments. The "the access is technically authorized; it's just not appropriate" framing is the operationally-correct framing for the entire detection problem.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    551[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    552[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe eight-paragraph "the reason this problem lands at the complex end of the chapter" subsection (the base rate is brutal; legitimate access patterns are extraordinarily diverse; the treatment relationship is poorly captured in source data; the data is high-dimensional and multi-modal; adversarial dynamics matter; the output isn't an alert, it's an investigation; workforce monitoring has its own legal and labor considerations; the breach notification clock is real; HIPAA Security Rule audit controls are mandatory but underspecified) is the densest treatment of healthcare-access-monitoring complexity anywhere in the cookbook.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    553[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    554[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Detection Pattern Catalog subsection (seventeen named patterns with per-pattern operational caveats) is the most comprehensive enumeration of healthcare access-pattern detection categories in any cookbook recipe. The per-pattern operational caveats (same-name pattern weighted by name uniqueness, same-address pattern requiring HR address linkage, self-access pattern's policy-dependence, etc.) are specific and operationally accurate.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    555[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    556[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Statistical and ML Methods subsection is a layered architecture posture done right. The closing "reasonable layered architecture" recommendation (rules engine first, baselines second, graph third, sequence fourth, LLM triage fifth, supervised classifier when labels are sufficient) is operations-engineer voice on the most consequential program-design decision.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    557[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    558[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Identity, Patient, and Workforce Enrichment subsection is the operationally-correct enumeration of the data sources that drive enrichment quality.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    559[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    560[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Calibration, Subgroup Performance, and the Workforce-Equity Question subsection is unusually substantive on the workforce-equity dimension. The "the workforce members being monitored are often the same employees the organization is trying to retain and engage" framing and the four-pattern treatment is the operationally-honest framing.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    561[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    562[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Workflow-Integration-Is-Again-The-Actual-Product subsection lands the same lesson as Recipes 3.6, 3.7, and 3.8 with an access-monitoring-specific factoring.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    563[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    564[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Honest Take is publication-ready voice. The thirteen lessons (build the program first then the technology; the workforce member is the sensitive population; same-name and same-address rules are surprisingly high-yield; the sophisticated cases are rare and often caught by accident; care-relationship data is the longest-running pain point; privileged users are a different program; LLM-assisted triage is the biggest near-term productivity improvement; biggest mistake is flooding the workforce with investigations; the political reality is CISO-and-CPO joint function; training-data scarcity is a real constraint; mature programs make the false-positive rate a leading indicator; start narrower than usual; the financial story has changed; patients matter most even when invisible) are the right teaching priorities.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    565[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    566[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe closing "patients matter most, even when they're invisible in the operational workflow" framing is the kind of moral-clarity framing that distinguishes the cookbook from documentation; "the patients whose privacy is being protected are mostly invisible to the operational machinery. They show up only when something goes wrong (they call to complain, they get notified of a breach, they file a suit). The program's purpose is to protect them. The operational ethic should reflect that, even when the day-to-day work doesn't bring them into the room" is operations-engineer voice on the highest-value lesson in the access-monitoring domain.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    567[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    568[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Variations and Extensions section covers fourteen adjacent patterns at substantive depth. The "Vendor-tool augmentation rather than replacement" framing is the operationally-honest framing for the build-vs-buy decision. The closed-loop framing for closed-loop interventions is appropriately cautious. The patient-facing transparency framing acknowledges the tradeoffs honestly.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    569[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    570[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mStyle hygiene is exceptionally clean: zero em dashes (verified directly with U+2014 character check; zero matches), zero en dashes (U+2013 verified), no marketing language, no documentation-voice. The 70/30 vendor balance is preserved cleanly. HTML-comment TODO discipline is correct (sixteen TODOs total, all forward-placeholder, no bracket-style visible TODOs). The TODOs cluster sensibly: NLRB workforce-monitoring guidance and state employee privacy statutes; current state breach notification timelines; OCR enforcement actions on inadequate audit controls; current state-of-the-art for GNN-based insider threat detection; specific published work on LLM-assisted patient-privacy-monitoring triage; HIPAA-eligibility status of Neptune, Timestream, and Bedrock foundation models; recent OCR settlement amounts; aws-samples or aws-solutions-library-samples repositories; AWS blog posts on UEBA or patient-privacy monitoring; specific peer-reviewed citations.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    571[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    572[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mFinding V1: Sample Output Future-Dated Timestamps and Identifiers[K
