[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    633[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    634[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Either (a) tighten the sample narrative to land further from the routing-recommendation boundary (replace "Recommended for privacy office same-day review" with "Access pattern is inconsistent with documented care-team relationships and presents multiple deviation indicators (off-shift access, weak care relationship, household-level demographic match). The pattern description supports the calibration-and-tier-mapping layer's tier assignment."), or (b) keep the sample as-is but add an inline note in the prose above the sample explaining the boundary: "The closing phrase 'Recommended for privacy office same-day review' sits at the constraint boundary; some privacy-office governance committees prefer narratives that stop at pattern description and let the calibration-and-tier-mapping layer make the routing decision. The exact phrasing is a privacy-office-governance decision; the LLM constraints are tuned per institution." Option (a) is the smaller editorial change and aligns with the more-conservative posture; option (b) preserves the sample but makes the boundary explicit.[K
