[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    843[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe risk profile is comparable to Recipes 3.6, 3.7, and 3.8 in clinical-safety consequence terms (missed breaches lead to harms; over-flagging produces wrongful-investigation labor exposure) but distinct in workforce-equity terms (the population being monitored is the workforce, which creates labor-relations and disparate-impact concerns), in regulatory-framework-breadth terms (the broadest in the chapter; HIPAA Security Rule, HIPAA Privacy Rule, HIPAA Breach Notification, ECPA, state employee privacy statutes, NLRB, collective bargaining), and in self-monitoring terms (the monitoring-system-access logs are themselves part of the program's evidentiary basis). The recipe's prose framing addresses all four elevated risks correctly; the operational-completeness backstops (privileged-user separate program, account-class enrichment, new-user ramp-up handling, care-relationship suppression-rule schema-and-workflow, idempotency, DLQs, reference-data versioning, case payload PHI-and-workforce-PII minimization, subgroup governance, self-monitoring) are the right next-pass priorities.[K
